put.description:
Update column metadata such as display name, description, tags, glossary terms, and other properties. This API works for columns in both tables and dashboard data models. The column is identified by its fully qualified name and the parent entity type is specified. 

Tag Management Examples:
• Add tags: {"tags": [{"tagFQN": "PersonalData.PII", "source": "Classification"}]}
• Remove specific tag: {"tags": []} (specify only tags you want to keep)
• Remove all tags: {"tags": []}
• Mix classifications and glossary terms: {"tags": [{"tagFQN": "PII.Sensitive", "source": "Classification"}, {"tagFQN": "Glossary.CustomerData", "source": "Glossary"}]}
• Don't change tags: omit the 'tags' field entirely

Validation Rules:
• Invalid or non-existent tags/glossary terms will result in a 404 error
• All tags and glossary terms must exist and be valid before the request succeeds
